DarkMouse::

She stopped and stared at Quickstrike. She cuoldn't believe her audio 
receptors. "She's your what?"
She had a slight look of shock on her face. "Quickstrike, you and 
her?" She frowned and looked down. "You my friend Quickstrike." She 
sighed heavily. She felt her spark break, but she didn't want to show 
it to him. She thought that he wouldn't care anyhow. She said in a 
quiet voice. "I'll follow you commander, where ever you lead, I'll 
follow." She didn't look back up at him. 


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, wilddance_mare@h... wrote:
> Quickstrike:
> 
> 
> 
> Quickstrike glared a little harshly at Dark Mouse. He didn't like 
the 
> sound of this, but he had a feeling that Black Arachnia could 
handle 
> this. He knew how treachrous she was. 
> 
> "Listen," he said to her. "She's mah mate an' leader. Ah know she 
> ain't on their side. Most certainly not on Hell Beast. He was gonna 
> kill 'er. She's gonna do somethin', ah got uh feelin'. Ah jus' need 
> t' find out. Ah's been kept outta this fer some reason, but ah'm 
> gonna get inta it. Ah was busy back at base wit' Rattrap. Black 
> Arachnia ain't no traitor t' us. Ah know she ain't. But if 
somethin' 
> goes wrong, an' ya think somethin's gonna happen, ya can jus' 
leave. 
> Ya don't have t' stick by me if somethin' gonna blow by yer head, 
> hear? Ah'll stay 'til ah get uh gun t' mah head, that's th' way ah 
> am. Ah'm used t' it. Ah'm second in command, ah gotta stick by 
Black 
> Arachnia. But ah can still save mah own tail. Ah jus' trust her a 
> lot. Ya don't understand how much ah missed her. An' ya don't have 
> t'. Ah jus' need t' get back wit' her and find out what's th' plan."
>
